cheatSheet.damage.content.table.damage1Plus.content=The model is injured. Mark the model with damage counters equal to the actual damage caused.
cheatSheet.damage.content.table.damagebiggersize.title=> Size
cheatSheet.damage.content.table.damagebiggersize.content=The model is removed from the game.

cheatSheet.fightmodifiers.title=Fight Modifiers
cheatSheet.fightmodifiers.content1=<p>These dice modifiers are the same  for both <b>Fight</b> and <b>Survive</b> tests.</p>\
   <p><b>Pinned models</b> stand up for free, but can only make <b>Survive</b> tests.</p>
cheatSheet.fightmodifiers.content2=<li>+1 Dice if the model moved into this cube in this action</li>\
  <li>+1 Dice if any friendly models are in the same cube (mqx +1 dice, not +1 dice per friendly model)</li>\
  <li>+1 dice if opponent is injured</li>\
  <li>+1 dice if the model is larger size than its openent</li>\
  <li>+1 dice if the opposing model is pinned</li>\
  <li>for Horde models +1 dice per model, that also has Horde</li>


cheatSheet.slammedIntoWall.title=Slammed into wall
cheatSheet.slammedIntoWall.content1=<p>The wall rolls 3 dice 5+ test (X)</p>
cheatSheet.slammedIntoWall.content2=<li><b>Draw or Survivor wins:</b> The model is unharmed</li>\
  <li><b>Wall wins:</b> The model is Pinned, and the difference in number of successes is the potential damage.</li>

cheatSheet.falling.title=Falling
cheatSheet.falling.content1=<p>Gravity rolls 3 dice 5+ test (X) with +1 dice per cube the model falls.</p>
cheatSheet.falling.content2=<li><b>Draw or Survivor wins:</b> The model is Pinned.</li>\
  <li><b>Gravity wins:</b> The model is Pinned, and the difference in number of successes is the potential damage.</li>

cheatSheet.knockback.title=Knockback
cheatSheet.knockback.content=Apply Knockback only when the attack causes potential damage.

cheatSheet.frag.title=Frag (X)
cheatSheet.frag.content1=<p>Roll a variable dice 4+ test (X) for the strength of the attack, where the number of dice rolled is the number in brackets after Frag.</p>
cheatSheet.frag.content2=<li>Whatever the results of the explosion is, all surviving models in the target cube are thrown on cube in a random direction and are then Pinned.</li>\
  <li><b>Draw or target wins:</b> The model is unharmed.</li>\
  <li><b>Frag wins:</b> The difference in number of successes is the potential damage.</li>

